        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
It is very true that 99.99999% of the time, a point can be very properly articulated in a civil and polite fashion.  Profanity does not really serve much of a purpose other then to allow a venting of frustration and colorful metaphors, but really just lowers the general intelect of the post and expections from those that post in that fashion.  

The English language is diverse and colorful.  There are plenty other ways to express opinions about someone, then using profanity.  Calling someone a toe-jam licker, or wart in the arm-pit of a festering hag, tend to bring up some wonderful imagery.  

The ingenious use of the standard keyboard to bypass such language filters can also prove to be quite entertaining.  

Basically, we are all (generally) treated and expected to act as adults on this board and, believe it or not, in game.  I don't mind the language filter.  If you have to use profanity to get your point accross, spend 20 seconds working on a way to bypass the language filter, or spend 20 seconds using a thesaurus or a dictionary.  

Please note, that profanity is sometimes oddly fitting.  Eg. the post where some group leader was going to boot the Necro when they found a suitable replacement.  In that case the group leader really was a w-a-n-k-e-r.  





<A target=B href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95266" >[img]http://www.isomedia.com/homes/kuoman/Kuotat.jpg[/img]</a>
[/quote]</textarea><br>
        </td>
