        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> there really is no rational reason to have a language filter. your eyes aren't going to start gushing blood, your kids won't start raping little old ladies if they read it, and you won't get struck by lightning. <BR>'colorful metaphors' are a vibrant part of the english language, and express emotions in ways no other words can. an example:</P><P>i'm riding with my sister and her fiance, he's driving and i'm in back seat behind him. he pulls up to a stop sign and begins to pull out to the right, but i see a car coming that he obviously didn't. now i could have said, 'gosh, lookout dave!'.. but no.. i said, 'lookout, oh F U C K!'.. needless to say he got the message and hit the brakes. </P><P>bottom line is it's expression. if you have some kind of moral hang up about it, find it naughty, distasteful, ingnorant, or stupid.. well you're just going to have to get over it. they're just little words, they won't bite.</P><P><table><tr><td><img src="http://xena.ipns.com/~snag/dave/SnagSig.jpg"></td><td align=center><BR>-Snag L'puss <br><BR>Leezurd Warlock <br><BR>-Weirzbowskey Nerfme<br><BR>54 pally</td></tr></table><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77614" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77614</a></font></td>
